<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,603]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,328,344,370]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species can be separated from most congeneric species by the presence of cone-shaped tubercles on the posterior corners of the carapace. There are three other 
<taxonomicName box="[996,1104,384,409]" class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Opopaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[996,1104,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">Opopaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<taxonomicName box="[1212,1393,384,409]" class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Opopaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diaoluoshan" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1212,1393,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">O. diaoluoshan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="2" pageNumber="25" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Tong &amp; Li, 2008" authorityName="Tong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2008" box="[220,583,422,448]" class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Opopaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbifera">
<emphasis box="[220,369,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">O. gibbifera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tong" box="[378,583,422,448]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" refString="Tong, Y. F. &amp; Li, S. Q. (2008) The oonopid spiders (Araneae: Oonopidae) from Hainan Island, China. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 56, 55 - 66." type="journal article" year="2008">
Tong &amp; Li, 
<number box="[523,583,422,448]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[643,798,423,448]" class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Opopaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitrispina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[643,798,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">O. vitrispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[806,904,422,448]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[806,904,422,448]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
) with similar characters. 
<taxonomicName box="[1217,1349,423,448]" class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Opopaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis box="[1217,1349,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">O. cornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from them by the following characters: large tubercles on carapace (compare 
<figureCitation box="[1296,1421,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 A – U" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,167,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[191,1397,167,1849]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 A – U. Opopaea cornuta Yin &amp; Wang, 1984 (B, K); Opopaea deserticola Simon, 1891 (Q, S, T); Opopaea diaoluoshan sp. nov. (C, H, I); Opopaea furcula sp. nov. (E, O); Opopaea gibbifera Tong &amp; Li, 2008 (D, L); Opopaea sanya sp. nov. (F, M); Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974 (G, N, P, R, U) and Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. (A, J). A – G. Male habitus, dorsal view; H. Male abdomen, ventral view; I – O. Male habitus, lateral view; P, Q. Male left palp, prolateral view; R, S. Female genitalia, ventral view; T, U. Female carapace, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205794/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
Figs 
<date box="[1358,1380,461,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
<number box="[1358,1369,461,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
I
</date>
–L
</figureCitation>
), clypeus height about 
<number box="[406,443,500,526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times of ALE diameter (
<figureCitation box="[743,880,500,526]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 A – U" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,167,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[191,1397,167,1849]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 A – U. Opopaea cornuta Yin &amp; Wang, 1984 (B, K); Opopaea deserticola Simon, 1891 (Q, S, T); Opopaea diaoluoshan sp. nov. (C, H, I); Opopaea furcula sp. nov. (E, O); Opopaea gibbifera Tong &amp; Li, 2008 (D, L); Opopaea sanya sp. nov. (F, M); Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974 (G, N, P, R, U) and Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. (A, J). A – G. Male habitus, dorsal view; H. Male abdomen, ventral view; I – O. Male habitus, lateral view; P, Q. Male left palp, prolateral view; R, S. Female genitalia, ventral view; T, U. Female carapace, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205794/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
Figs 
<number box="[804,816,500,526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
B, K
</figureCitation>
), epigastric area of female with a dark spot on postgynal plate (
<figureCitation box="[345,436,538,564]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 A – G" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[235,1372,155,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[228,1379,149,1941]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – G. Opopaea cornuta Yin &amp; Wang, 1984 (A – E) and Opopaea gibbifera Tong &amp; Li, 2008 (F – G). A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; D, G. Female postgynum, ventral view; E, F. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205795/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[399,414,538,564]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
D
</figureCitation>
) and outgrowths on male palpal embolus (
<figureCitation box="[936,1068,538,564]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 A – G" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[235,1372,155,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[228,1379,149,1941]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – G. Opopaea cornuta Yin &amp; Wang, 1984 (A – E) and Opopaea gibbifera Tong &amp; Li, 2008 (F – G). A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; D, G. Female postgynum, ventral view; E, F. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205795/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
Figs 
<number box="[995,1010,538,564]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
A, B
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
